# Universal Tools project rules

## Brand
- Product name: **Universal Tools** (mark: **UT**)
- Theme: Nextcloud-inspired (`#0082C9`, `#1CAFFF`, Inter) — do **not** use Nextcloud logos or trademarks
- Quality and UX are the priority over feature chrome
- **Never** reintroduce upstream product identity: old product name/logos/favicons, Locize project IDs, hire-me / tip CTAs, sponsor badges, Discord invite for upstream, or their demo domain

## UI vs functionality
- **UI is original.** Never copy layouts or marketing chrome from `references/upstream`.
- **Functionality may be copied** from that reference: tool algorithms, `defineTool` metadata, processing pipelines, and route contracts (`/{category}/{path}`).
- Prefer the **app shell + nested sidebar** navigation.

## Navigation
- Sidebar modules group tools for UX; Image merges `image-generic` + `png`; PDF is all `pdf` tools; other categories each get their own expandable module.
- Keep tool route paths and processing logic stable when redesigning chrome.

## Shell
- Persistent left sidebar on every page (temporary Drawer on mobile)
- Top bar: UT logo, search, theme, language
- Dashboard home is clean and modern
